title: Launch of NASA’s Psyche asteroid mission delayed to late September
summary: The launch of NASA’s Psyche asteroid mission, which was set for Aug. 1 on a SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket, has been delayed to no earlier than Sept. 20 after ground teams discovered an issue during software testing on the spacecraft, officials said Monday.

title: Lockheed Martin, Filecoin Foundation plan demonstration of decentralized data storage in space
summary: Lockheed Martin is working with the Filecoin Foundation to demonstrate an open-source blockchain network in space.

title: Russian spy satellite launched by Soyuz rocket
summary: A classified mapping satellite rode a Soyuz rocket into space Thursday from the Plesetsk Cosmodrome, the fifth space mission of the year to deploy a Russian military payload into orbit.

title: President Biden: NASA to Welcome Japanese Astronaut Aboard Gateway
summary: President Joe Biden and Japanese Prime Minister Fumio Kishida met in Tokyo Monday where they announced progress on collaboration for human and robotic lunar missions.
